OASISFormat:  0.4
OCamlVersion: >= 4.02.3
Name:         oak
Version:      0.1
Maintainers:  Izaak Meckler
Homepage:     http://parametricity.com
Synopsis:     An ocaml clone of Elm's collage library, for drawing with HTML's canvas.
Authors:      ihmeckler@gmail.com
License:      BSD-3-clause
Plugins:      META (0.4), DevFiles (0.4)
AlphaFeatures: ocamlbuild_more_args
XOCamlbuildPluginTags: package(js_of_ocaml), package(js_of_ocaml.syntax), package(js_of_ocaml.ocamlbuild)

Description:
  Oak is a library for drawing using the HTML canvas. One builds up
  a data structure that declaratively represents the drawing (a bit like SVG)
  and then renders it to a given canvas node.

Library "oak"
  Path: src
  BuildTools:ocamlbuild
  Modules: Oak
  InternalModules: Affine, Color, Either, Image, Iterator, Matrix, Vector
  BuildDepends: js_of_ocaml, js_of_ocaml.ppx
